title: 79.362 WORKERS' COMPENSATION REINSURANCE ASSOCIATION EXCESS SURPLUS DISTRIBUTION.
text: An order of the commissioner of the Department of Labor and Industry relating to the distribution of excess surplus of the Workers' Compensation Reinsurance Association shall be reviewed by the commissioner of commerce. The commissioner of commerce may amend, approve, or reject an order or issue further orders to accomplish the purposes of section 79.361 and Laws 1993, chapter 361, section 2. The commissioner may not change the amount of the distribution ordered by the commissioner of labor and industry without agreement of the commissioner of labor and industry.
